seed_data.description: “We think AI agents can be 10x employees,” says Jesse Zhang, cofounder and CEO of Decagon. That's why Zhang, 27, named his company, which builds customer service bots, after the 10-sided geometric shape. The startup's pitch to corporate clients, which include public companies like Duolingo and Hertz alongside buzzy startups such as Notion and Rippling, is that its AI can help consumers return products, cancel subscriptions or order replacement credit cards. Zhang says his secret sauce is that Decagon's bots can appear to empathize with frustrated users—which is more than can be said of the average call center employee. “We give a very, very personalized experience.”
